---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import GradientDivider from "../components/GradientDivider.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Lystaria"
  description="Privacy policy for the Lystaria iOS app."
>
  <main class="home-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="hero-text">Last updated: April 30, 2025</p>
    </section>

    <GradientDivider />

    <section class="prose-section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        Lystaria is a personal wellness and productivity app built for iOS. This
        privacy policy explains what data Lystaria collects, where it lives, and
        how it is used. The short version: your personal data stays on your
        device and in your iCloud account. Lystaria does not sell your data,
        does not serve you ads, and does not share your information with third
        parties for any commercial purpose.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Data You Create in Lystaria</h2>
      <p>
        Everything you log, write, or track in Lystaria — journal entries, mood
        logs, habits, reminders, calendar events, notes, reading sessions,
        health metrics, medications, symptom logs, checklists, bookmarks, and
        all other personal content — is stored locally on your device using
        SwiftData. If you are signed in with iCloud, this data syncs to your
        private iCloud account via CloudKit. At no point is this data
        transmitted to Lystaria's servers or any third party.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>iCloud and CloudKit</h2>
      <p>
        Lystaria uses Apple's CloudKit framework to sync your data across your
        devices. This sync occurs between your device and your personal iCloud
        account, which is managed entirely by Apple. Lystaria does not have
        access to your CloudKit data. Apple's privacy policy governs how iCloud
        handles your data. You can review it at
        <a
          href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">apple.com/legal/privacy</a
        >.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Apple HealthKit</h2>
      <p>
        Lystaria integrates with Apple HealthKit to read and write
        health-related data including step count, water intake, sleep data,
        heart rate variability, resting heart rate, and exercise sessions. This
        data is accessed only with your explicit permission and is used solely
        to power features within the app such as the sleep score card, daily
        completion tracking, body state analysis, and health streaks. Lystaria
        does not transmit HealthKit data to any server, and it is never used for
        advertising or shared with third parties.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Apple Sign In</h2>
      <p>
        Lystaria uses Sign in with Apple for account authentication. When you
        sign in, Apple provides Lystaria with a unique user identifier and,
        optionally, your name. Lystaria does not receive your Apple ID email
        address unless you choose to share it. This identifier is stored locally
        on your device to associate your data with your account. No
        authentication data is transmitted to external servers by Lystaria.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Horoscope and Astrology Content</h2>
      <p>
        If you use the Daily Astrology feature, Lystaria sends a request to a
        third-party horoscope API to fetch a reading for your selected zodiac
        sign. This request includes only the zodiac sign name — no personal
        identifiers, account information, or device data is included. The
        response is stored locally on your device for the day and is not shared
        further.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Widgets</h2>
      <p>
        Lystaria includes home screen and lock screen widgets that display
        information such as your last mood log date, reading progress, and
        health data. Widget data is shared between the main app and the widget
        extension using a shared App Group stored locally on your device. No
        widget data is transmitted externally.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Data We Do Not Collect</h2>
      <p>
        Lystaria does not collect analytics, crash reports, usage data, device
        identifiers, advertising identifiers, IP addresses, or any form of
        behavioral tracking. There are no third-party analytics SDKs integrated
        into Lystaria.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>In-App Purchases</h2>
      <p>
        Lystaria offers an optional premium subscription through Apple's
        StoreKit framework. All payment processing is handled entirely by Apple.
        Lystaria does not collect, store, or have access to any payment or
        billing information.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Lystaria is not directed at children under the age of 13 and does not
        knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a
        child has used Lystaria and provided personal information, please
        contact us so we can take appropriate action.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Data Deletion</h2>
      <p>
        Because Lystaria stores all data locally on your device and in your
        personal iCloud account, you have full control over your data at all
        times. You can delete individual entries, logs, or records from within
        the app. Deleting the app from your device removes all locally stored
        data. To remove iCloud data, you can manage your iCloud storage directly
        through iOS Settings.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        If this privacy policy changes in a meaningful way, the updated version
        will be published here with a revised date at the top of the page.
        Continued use of Lystaria after changes are posted constitutes
        acceptance of the updated policy.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this privacy policy or how Lystaria handles
        your data, you can reach out at
        <a href="mailto:contact@lystaria.im">contact@lystaria.im</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="policy-page-break" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <section class="prose-section">
      <h1 class="hero-title">Lurelia Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="hero-text">Last updated: May 19, 2026</p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        Lurelia is a personal productivity and life organization app designed
        for iOS. This privacy policy explains what information Lurelia accesses,
        where your data is stored, and how it is used. Your information belongs
        to you. Lurelia does not sell personal data, serve advertisements, or
        share your information with third parties for marketing purposes.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Data You Create in Lurelia</h2>
      <p>
        Information you create inside Lurelia — including reminders, habits,
        routines, tasks, Kanban boards, time blocks, rewards, productivity
        history, and app preferences — is stored locally on your device.
      </p>

      <p>
        If iCloud synchronization is enabled, your data may also securely sync
        to your personal iCloud account using Apple's CloudKit framework.
      </p>

      <p>
        Lurelia does not store your personal productivity data on external
        developer-controlled servers.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>iCloud and CloudKit</h2>
      <p>
        Lurelia uses Apple's CloudKit framework to synchronize your information
        across your Apple devices through your personal iCloud account.
      </p>

      <p>
        The developer of Lurelia does not have direct access to your private
        CloudKit data.
      </p>

      <p>
        Apple's handling of iCloud information is governed by Apple's privacy
        policy available at
        <a
          href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">apple.com/legal/privacy</a
        >.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Notifications and Scheduling</h2>
      <p>
        Lurelia uses local notifications to deliver reminders, routine prompts,
        habit check-ins, scheduled tasks, and time-sensitive alerts.
      </p>

      <p>
        Notification scheduling occurs directly on your device and notification
        content is not transmitted to external servers.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Widgets</h2>
      <p>
        Lurelia may include home screen or lock screen widgets displaying
        reminders, routines, habits, schedules, progress information, and task
        activity.
      </p>

      <p>
        Widget information is shared locally between the app and widget
        extensions using Apple's App Group system.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>In-App Purchases</h2>
      <p>
        Lurelia may offer optional premium features or subscriptions through
        Apple's StoreKit framework. Payment processing is handled entirely by
        Apple.
      </p>

      <p>
        Lurelia does not collect or store payment information, billing details,
        or credit card numbers.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Analytics and Tracking</h2>
      <p>
        Lurelia does not use advertising SDKs or third-party behavioral tracking
        systems.
      </p>

      <p>
        If anonymous analytics or crash diagnostics are introduced in the future
        to improve app performance or stability, this policy will be updated
        accordingly.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Lurelia is not directed toward children under the age of 13 and does not
        knowingly collect personal information from children.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Data Deletion</h2>
      <p>
        You maintain control over your information at all times. You may delete
        reminders, habits, routines, tasks, and other content directly within
        the app.
      </p>

      <p>
        Deleting the app removes locally stored data from your device. If iCloud
        synchronization is enabled, synced data can also be managed through your
        Apple ID and iCloud settings.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        This privacy policy may occasionally be updated to reflect feature
        changes, legal requirements, or platform updates. Updated versions will
        be published on this page with a revised effective date.
      </p>

      <GradientDivider />

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this privacy policy or how Lurelia handles
        your information, you can contact:
      </p>

      <p>
        <a href="mailto:contact@lystaria.im">contact@lystaria.im</a>
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</DocsLayout>
